39// Determines whether we have seen at least the given maximum number of
40// pings fail to have a response.
41inline bool TooManyFailures(
42 const std::vector<cricket::Connection::SentPing>& pings_since_last_response,
43 uint32_t maximum_failures,
44 int rtt_estimate,
45 int64_t now) {
46 // If we haven't sent that many pings, then we can't have failed that many.
47 if (pings_since_last_response.size() < maximum_failures)
48 return false;
49
50 // Check if the window in which we would expect a response to the ping has
51 // already elapsed.
52 int64_t expected_response_time =
53 pings_since_last_response[maximum_failures - 1].sent_time + rtt_estimate;
54 return now > expected_response_time;
55}
56
57// Determines whether we have gone too long without seeing any response.
58inline bool TooLongWithoutResponse(
59 const std::vector<cricket::Connection::SentPing>& pings_since_last_response,
60 int64_t maximum_time,
61 int64_t now) {
62 if (pings_since_last_response.size() == 0)
63 return false;
64
65 auto first = pings_since_last_response[0];
66 return now > (first.sent_time + maximum_time);
67}

69// Helper methods for converting string values of log description fields to
70// enum.
71webrtc::IceCandidateType GetCandidateTypeByString(const std::string& type) {
72 if (type == cricket::LOCAL_PORT_TYPE) {
73 return webrtc::IceCandidateType::kLocal;
74 } else if (type == cricket::STUN_PORT_TYPE) {
75 return webrtc::IceCandidateType::kStun;
76 } else if (type == cricket::PRFLX_PORT_TYPE) {
77 return webrtc::IceCandidateType::kPrflx;
78 } else if (type == cricket::RELAY_PORT_TYPE) {
79 return webrtc::IceCandidateType::kRelay;
80 }
81 return webrtc::IceCandidateType::kUnknown;
82}
83
84webrtc::IceCandidatePairProtocol GetProtocolByString(
85 const std::string& protocol) {
86 if (protocol == cricket::UDP_PROTOCOL_NAME) {
87 return webrtc::IceCandidatePairProtocol::kUdp;
88 } else if (protocol == cricket::TCP_PROTOCOL_NAME) {
89 return webrtc::IceCandidatePairProtocol::kTcp;
90 } else if (protocol == cricket::SSLTCP_PROTOCOL_NAME) {
91 return webrtc::IceCandidatePairProtocol::kSsltcp;
92 } else if (protocol == cricket::TLS_PROTOCOL_NAME) {
93 return webrtc::IceCandidatePairProtocol::kTls;
94 }
95 return webrtc::IceCandidatePairProtocol::kUnknown;
96}
97
98webrtc::IceCandidatePairAddressFamily GetAddressFamilyByInt(
99 int address_family) {
100 if (address_family == AF_INET) {
101 return webrtc::IceCandidatePairAddressFamily::kIpv4;
102 } else if (address_family == AF_INET6) {
103 return webrtc::IceCandidatePairAddressFamily::kIpv6;
104 }
105 return webrtc::IceCandidatePairAddressFamily::kUnknown;
106}
107
108webrtc::IceCandidateNetworkType ConvertNetworkType(rtc::AdapterType type) {
109 switch (type) {
110 case rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_ETHERNET:
111 return webrtc::IceCandidateNetworkType::kEthernet;
112 case rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_LOOPBACK:
113 return webrtc::IceCandidateNetworkType::kLoopback;
114 case rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_WIFI:
115 return webrtc::IceCandidateNetworkType::kWifi;
116 case rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_VPN:
117 return webrtc::IceCandidateNetworkType::kVpn;
118 case rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_CELLULAR:
119 case rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_CELLULAR_2G:
120 case rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_CELLULAR_3G:
121 case rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_CELLULAR_4G:
122 case rtc::ADAPTER_TYPE_CELLULAR_5G:
123 return webrtc::IceCandidateNetworkType::kCellular;
124 default:
125 return webrtc::IceCandidateNetworkType::kUnknown;
126 }
127}

129// When we don't have any RTT data, we have to pick something reasonable. We
130// use a large value just in case the connection is really slow.
131const int DEFAULT_RTT = 3000; // 3 seconds
132
133// We will restrict RTT estimates (when used for determining state) to be
134// within a reasonable range.
135const int MINIMUM_RTT = 100; // 0.1 seconds
136const int MAXIMUM_RTT = 60000; // 60 seconds
137
138const int DEFAULT_RTT_ESTIMATE_HALF_TIME_MS = 500;
139
140// Computes our estimate of the RTT given the current estimate.
141inline int ConservativeRTTEstimate(int rtt) {
142 return rtc::SafeClamp(2 * rtt, MINIMUM_RTT, MAXIMUM_RTT);
143}
144
145// Weighting of the old rtt value to new data.
146const int RTT_RATIO = 3; // 3 : 1
147
148constexpr int64_t kMinExtraPingDelayMs = 100;
149
150// Default field trials.
151const cricket::IceFieldTrials kDefaultFieldTrials;
152
153constexpr int kSupportGoogPingVersionRequestIndex =
154 static_cast<int>(cricket::IceGoogMiscInfoBindingRequestAttributeIndex::
155 SUPPORT_GOOG_PING_VERSION);
156
157constexpr int kSupportGoogPingVersionResponseIndex =
158 static_cast<int>(cricket::IceGoogMiscInfoBindingResponseAttributeIndex::
159 SUPPORT_GOOG_PING_VERSION);

165// A ConnectionRequest is a STUN binding used to determine writability.
166ConnectionRequest::ConnectionRequest(Connection* connection)
167 : StunRequest(new IceMessage()), connection_(connection) {}

169void ConnectionRequest::Prepare(StunMessage* request) {
170 request->SetType(STUN_BINDING_REQUEST);
171 std::string username;
172 connection_->port()->CreateStunUsername(
173 connection_->remote_candidate().username(), &username);
174 // Note that the order of attributes does not impact the parsing on the
175 // receiver side. The attribute is retrieved then by iterating and matching
176 // over all parsed attributes. See StunMessage::GetAttribute.
177 request->AddAttribute(
178 std::make_unique<StunByteStringAttribute>(STUN_ATTR_USERNAME, username));
179
180 // connection_ already holds this ping, so subtract one from count.
181 if (connection_->port()->send_retransmit_count_attribute()) {
182 request->AddAttribute(std::make_unique<StunUInt32Attribute>(
183 STUN_ATTR_RETRANSMIT_COUNT,
184 static_cast<uint32_t>(connection_->pings_since_last_response_.size() -
185 1)));
186 }
187 uint32_t network_info = connection_->port()->Network()->id();
188 network_info = (network_info << 16) | connection_->port()->network_cost();
189 request->AddAttribute(std::make_unique<StunUInt32Attribute>(
190 STUN_ATTR_GOOG_NETWORK_INFO, network_info));
191
192 if (webrtc::field_trial::IsEnabled(
193 "WebRTC-PiggybackIceCheckAcknowledgement") &&
194 connection_->last_ping_id_received()) {
195 request->AddAttribute(std::make_unique<StunByteStringAttribute>(
196 STUN_ATTR_GOOG_LAST_ICE_CHECK_RECEIVED,
197 connection_->last_ping_id_received().value()));
198 }
199
200 // Adding ICE_CONTROLLED or ICE_CONTROLLING attribute based on the role.
201 if (connection_->port()->GetIceRole() == ICEROLE_CONTROLLING) {
202 request->AddAttribute(std::make_unique<StunUInt64Attribute>(
203 STUN_ATTR_ICE_CONTROLLING, connection_->port()->IceTiebreaker()));
204 // We should have either USE_CANDIDATE attribute or ICE_NOMINATION
205 // attribute but not both. That was enforced in p2ptransportchannel.
206 if (connection_->use_candidate_attr()) {
207 request->AddAttribute(
208 std::make_unique<StunByteStringAttribute>(STUN_ATTR_USE_CANDIDATE));
209 }
210 if (connection_->nomination() &&
211 connection_->nomination() != connection_->acked_nomination()) {
212 request->AddAttribute(std::make_unique<StunUInt32Attribute>(
213 STUN_ATTR_NOMINATION, connection_->nomination()));
214 }
215 } else if (connection_->port()->GetIceRole() == ICEROLE_CONTROLLED) {
216 request->AddAttribute(std::make_unique<StunUInt64Attribute>(
217 STUN_ATTR_ICE_CONTROLLED, connection_->port()->IceTiebreaker()));
218 } else {
219 RTC_NOTREACHED();
220 }
221
222 // Adding PRIORITY Attribute.
223 // Changing the type preference to Peer Reflexive and local preference
224 // and component id information is unchanged from the original priority.
225 // priority = (2^24)*(type preference) +
226 // (2^8)*(local preference) +
227 // (2^0)*(256 - component ID)
228 uint32_t type_preference =
229 (connection_->local_candidate().protocol() == TCP_PROTOCOL_NAME)
230 ? ICE_TYPE_PREFERENCE_PRFLX_TCP
231 : ICE_TYPE_PREFERENCE_PRFLX;
232 uint32_t prflx_priority =
233 type_preference << 24 |
234 (connection_->local_candidate().priority() & 0x00FFFFFF);
235 request->AddAttribute(std::make_unique<StunUInt32Attribute>(
236 STUN_ATTR_PRIORITY, prflx_priority));
237
238 if (connection_->field_trials_->enable_goog_ping &&
239 !connection_->remote_support_goog_ping_.has_value()) {
240 // Check if remote supports GOOG PING by announcing which version we
241 // support. This is sent on all STUN_BINDING_REQUEST until we get a
242 // STUN_BINDING_RESPONSE.
243 auto list =
244 StunAttribute::CreateUInt16ListAttribute(STUN_ATTR_GOOG_MISC_INFO);
245 list->AddTypeAtIndex(kSupportGoogPingVersionRequestIndex, kGoogPingVersion);
246 request->AddAttribute(std::move(list));
247 }
248
249 if (connection_->ShouldSendGoogPing(request)) {
250 request->SetType(GOOG_PING_REQUEST);
251 request->ClearAttributes();
252 request->AddMessageIntegrity32(connection_->remote_candidate().password());
253 } else {
254 request->AddMessageIntegrity(connection_->remote_candidate().password());
255 request->AddFingerprint();
256 }
257}

282Connection::Connection(Port* port,
283 size_t index,
284 const Candidate& remote_candidate)
285 : id_(rtc::CreateRandomId()),
286 port_(port),
287 local_candidate_index_(index),
288 remote_candidate_(remote_candidate),
289 recv_rate_tracker_(100, 10u),
290 send_rate_tracker_(100, 10u),
291 write_state_(STATE_WRITE_INIT),
292 receiving_(false),
293 connected_(true),
294 pruned_(false),
295 use_candidate_attr_(false),
296 remote_ice_mode_(ICEMODE_FULL),
297 requests_(port->thread()),
298 rtt_(DEFAULT_RTT),
299 last_ping_sent_(0),
300 last_ping_received_(0),
301 last_data_received_(0),
302 last_ping_response_received_(0),
303 reported_(false),
304 state_(IceCandidatePairState::WAITING),
305 time_created_ms_(rtc::TimeMillis()),
306 field_trials_(&kDefaultFieldTrials),
307 rtt_estimate_(DEFAULT_RTT_ESTIMATE_HALF_TIME_MS) {
308 // All of our connections start in WAITING state.
309 // TODO(mallinath) - Start connections from STATE_FROZEN.
310 // Wire up to send stun packets
311 requests_.SignalSendPacket.connect(this, &Connection::OnSendStunPacket);
312 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString() << ": Connection created";
313}

334uint64_t Connection::priority() const {
335 uint64_t priority = 0;
336 // RFC 5245 - 5.7.2. Computing Pair Priority and Ordering Pairs
337 // Let G be the priority for the candidate provided by the controlling
338 // agent. Let D be the priority for the candidate provided by the
339 // controlled agent.
340 // pair priority = 2^32*MIN(G,D) + 2*MAX(G,D) + (G>D?1:0)
341 IceRole role = port_->GetIceRole();
342 if (role != ICEROLE_UNKNOWN) {
343 uint32_t g = 0;
344 uint32_t d = 0;
345 if (role == ICEROLE_CONTROLLING) {
346 g = local_candidate().priority();
347 d = remote_candidate_.priority();
348 } else {
349 g = remote_candidate_.priority();
350 d = local_candidate().priority();
351 }
352 priority = std::min(g, d);
353 priority = priority << 32;
354 priority += 2 * std::max(g, d) + (g > d ? 1 : 0);
355 }
356 return priority;
357}

359void Connection::set_write_state(WriteState value) {
360 WriteState old_value = write_state_;
361 write_state_ = value;
362 if (value != old_value) {
363 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << ToString() << ": set_write_state from: " << old_value
364 << " to " << value;
365 SignalStateChange(this);
366 }

369void Connection::UpdateReceiving(int64_t now) {
370 bool receiving;
371 if (last_ping_sent() < last_ping_response_received()) {
372 // We consider any candidate pair that has its last connectivity check
373 // acknowledged by a response as receiving, particularly for backup
374 // candidate pairs that send checks at a much slower pace than the selected
375 // one. Otherwise, a backup candidate pair constantly becomes not receiving
376 // as a side effect of a long ping interval, since we do not have a separate
377 // receiving timeout for backup candidate pairs. See
378 // IceConfig.ice_backup_candidate_pair_ping_interval,
379 // IceConfig.ice_connection_receiving_timeout and their default value.
380 receiving = true;
381 } else {
382 receiving =
383 last_received() > 0 && now <= last_received() + receiving_timeout();
384 }
385 if (receiving_ == receiving) {
386 return;
387 }
388 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << ToString() << ": set_receiving to " << receiving;
389 receiving_ = receiving;
390 receiving_unchanged_since_ = now;
391 SignalStateChange(this);
392}

436void Connection::OnSendStunPacket(const void* data,
437 size_t size,
438 StunRequest* req) {
439 rtc::PacketOptions options(port_->StunDscpValue());
440 options.info_signaled_after_sent.packet_type =
441 rtc::PacketType::kIceConnectivityCheck;
442 auto err =
443 port_->SendTo(data, size, remote_candidate_.address(), options, false);
444 if (err < 0) {
445 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << ToString()
446 << ": Failed to send STUN ping "
447 " err="
448 << err << " id=" << rtc::hex_encode(req->id());
449 }
450}
451
452void Connection::OnReadPacket(const char* data,
453 size_t size,
454 int64_t packet_time_us) {
455 std::unique_ptr<IceMessage> msg;
456 std::string remote_ufrag;
457 const rtc::SocketAddress& addr(remote_candidate_.address());
458 if (!port_->GetStunMessage(data, size, addr, &msg, &remote_ufrag)) {
459 // The packet did not parse as a valid STUN message
460 // This is a data packet, pass it along.
461 last_data_received_ = rtc::TimeMillis();
462 UpdateReceiving(last_data_received_);
463 recv_rate_tracker_.AddSamples(size);
464 stats_.packets_received++;
465 SignalReadPacket(this, data, size, packet_time_us);
466
467 // If timed out sending writability checks, start up again
468 if (!pruned_ && (write_state_ == STATE_WRITE_TIMEOUT)) {
469 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
470 << "Received a data packet on a timed-out Connection. "
471 "Resetting state to STATE_WRITE_INIT.";
472 set_write_state(STATE_WRITE_INIT);
473 }
474 } else if (!msg) {
475 // The packet was STUN, but failed a check and was handled internally.
476 } else {
477 // The packet is STUN and passed the Port checks.
478 // Perform our own checks to ensure this packet is valid.
479 // If this is a STUN request, then update the receiving bit and respond.
480 // If this is a STUN response, then update the writable bit.
481 // Log at LS_INFO if we receive a ping on an unwritable connection.
482 rtc::LoggingSeverity sev = (!writable() ? rtc::LS_INFO : rtc::LS_VERBOSE);
483 msg->ValidateMessageIntegrity(remote_candidate().password());
484 switch (msg->type()) {
485 case STUN_BINDING_REQUEST:
486 RTC_LOG_V(sev) << ToString() << ": Received "
487 << StunMethodToString(msg->type())
488 << ", id=" << rtc::hex_encode(msg->transaction_id());
489 if (remote_ufrag == remote_candidate_.username()) {
490 HandleStunBindingOrGoogPingRequest(msg.get());
491 } else {
492 // The packet had the right local username, but the remote username
493 // was not the right one for the remote address.
494 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
495 << ToString()
496 << ": Received STUN request with bad remote username "
497 << remote_ufrag;
498 port_->SendBindingErrorResponse(msg.get(), addr,
499 STUN_ERROR_UNAUTHORIZED,
500 STUN_ERROR_REASON_UNAUTHORIZED);
501 }
502 break;
503
504 // Response from remote peer. Does it match request sent?
505 // This doesn't just check, it makes callbacks if transaction
506 // id's match.
507 case STUN_BINDING_RESPONSE:
508 case STUN_BINDING_ERROR_RESPONSE:
509 if (msg->IntegrityOk()) {
510 requests_.CheckResponse(msg.get());
511 }
512 // Otherwise silently discard the response message.
513 break;
514
515 // Remote end point sent an STUN indication instead of regular binding
516 // request. In this case |last_ping_received_| will be updated but no
517 // response will be sent.
518 case STUN_BINDING_INDICATION:
519 ReceivedPing(msg->transaction_id());
520 break;
521 case GOOG_PING_REQUEST:
522 HandleStunBindingOrGoogPingRequest(msg.get());
523 break;
524 case GOOG_PING_RESPONSE:
525 case GOOG_PING_ERROR_RESPONSE:
526 if (msg->IntegrityOk()) {
527 requests_.CheckResponse(msg.get());
528 }
529 break;
530 default:
531 RTC_NOTREACHED();
532 break;
533 }
534 }
535}
536
537void Connection::HandleStunBindingOrGoogPingRequest(IceMessage* msg) {
538 // This connection should now be receiving.
539 ReceivedPing(msg->transaction_id());
540 if (webrtc::field_trial::IsEnabled("WebRTC-ExtraICEPing") &&
541 last_ping_response_received_ == 0) {
542 if (local_candidate().type() == RELAY_PORT_TYPE ||
543 local_candidate().type() == PRFLX_PORT_TYPE ||
544 remote_candidate().type() == RELAY_PORT_TYPE ||
545 remote_candidate().type() == PRFLX_PORT_TYPE) {
546 const int64_t now = rtc::TimeMillis();
547 if (last_ping_sent_ + kMinExtraPingDelayMs <= now) {
548 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString()
549 << "WebRTC-ExtraICEPing/Sending extra ping"
550 " last_ping_sent_: "
551 << last_ping_sent_ << " now: " << now
552 << " (diff: " << (now - last_ping_sent_) << ")";
553 Ping(now);
554 } else {
555 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString()
556 << "WebRTC-ExtraICEPing/Not sending extra ping"
557 " last_ping_sent_: "
558 << last_ping_sent_ << " now: " << now
559 << " (diff: " << (now - last_ping_sent_) << ")";
560 }
561 }
562 }
563
564 const rtc::SocketAddress& remote_addr = remote_candidate_.address();
565 if (msg->type() == STUN_BINDING_REQUEST) {
566 // Check for role conflicts.
567 const std::string& remote_ufrag = remote_candidate_.username();
568 if (!port_->MaybeIceRoleConflict(remote_addr, msg, remote_ufrag)) {
569 // Received conflicting role from the peer.
570 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Received conflicting role from the peer.";
571 return;
572 }
573 }
574
575 stats_.recv_ping_requests++;
576 LogCandidatePairEvent(webrtc::IceCandidatePairEventType::kCheckReceived,
577 msg->reduced_transaction_id());
578
579 // This is a validated stun request from remote peer.
580 if (msg->type() == STUN_BINDING_REQUEST) {
581 SendStunBindingResponse(msg);
582 } else {
583 RTC_DCHECK(msg->type() == GOOG_PING_REQUEST);
584 SendGoogPingResponse(msg);
585 }
586
587 // If it timed out on writing check, start up again
588 if (!pruned_ && write_state_ == STATE_WRITE_TIMEOUT) {
589 set_write_state(STATE_WRITE_INIT);
590 }
591
592 if (port_->GetIceRole() == ICEROLE_CONTROLLED) {
593 const StunUInt32Attribute* nomination_attr =
594 msg->GetUInt32(STUN_ATTR_NOMINATION);
595 uint32_t nomination = 0;
596 if (nomination_attr) {
597 nomination = nomination_attr->value();
598 if (nomination == 0) {
599 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Invalid nomination: " << nomination;
600 }
601 } else {
602 const StunByteStringAttribute* use_candidate_attr =
603 msg->GetByteString(STUN_ATTR_USE_CANDIDATE);
604 if (use_candidate_attr) {
605 nomination = 1;
606 }
607 }
608 // We don't un-nominate a connection, so we only keep a larger nomination.
609 if (nomination > remote_nomination_) {
610 set_remote_nomination(nomination);
611 SignalNominated(this);
612 }
613 }
614 // Set the remote cost if the network_info attribute is available.
615 // Note: If packets are re-ordered, we may get incorrect network cost
616 // temporarily, but it should get the correct value shortly after that.
617 const StunUInt32Attribute* network_attr =
618 msg->GetUInt32(STUN_ATTR_GOOG_NETWORK_INFO);
619 if (network_attr) {
620 uint32_t network_info = network_attr->value();
621 uint16_t network_cost = static_cast<uint16_t>(network_info);
622 if (network_cost != remote_candidate_.network_cost()) {
623 remote_candidate_.set_network_cost(network_cost);
624 // Network cost change will affect the connection ranking, so signal
625 // state change to force a re-sort in P2PTransportChannel.
626 SignalStateChange(this);
627 }
628 }
629
630 if (webrtc::field_trial::IsEnabled(
631 "WebRTC-PiggybackIceCheckAcknowledgement")) {
632 HandlePiggybackCheckAcknowledgementIfAny(msg);
633 }
634}
635
636void Connection::SendStunBindingResponse(const StunMessage* request) {
637 RTC_DCHECK(request->type() == STUN_BINDING_REQUEST);
638
639 // Retrieve the username from the request.
640 const StunByteStringAttribute* username_attr =
641 request->GetByteString(STUN_ATTR_USERNAME);
642 RTC_DCHECK(username_attr != NULL);
643 if (username_attr == NULL) {
644 // No valid username, skip the response.
645 return;
646 }
647
648 // Fill in the response message.
649 StunMessage response;
650 response.SetType(STUN_BINDING_RESPONSE);
651 response.SetTransactionID(request->transaction_id());
652 const StunUInt32Attribute* retransmit_attr =
653 request->GetUInt32(STUN_ATTR_RETRANSMIT_COUNT);
654 if (retransmit_attr) {
655 // Inherit the incoming retransmit value in the response so the other side
656 // can see our view of lost pings.
657 response.AddAttribute(std::make_unique<StunUInt32Attribute>(
658 STUN_ATTR_RETRANSMIT_COUNT, retransmit_attr->value()));
659
660 if (retransmit_attr->value() > CONNECTION_WRITE_CONNECT_FAILURES) {
661 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO)
662 << ToString()
663 << ": Received a remote ping with high retransmit count: "
664 << retransmit_attr->value();
665 }
666 }
667
668 response.AddAttribute(std::make_unique<StunXorAddressAttribute>(
669 STUN_ATTR_XOR_MAPPED_ADDRESS, remote_candidate_.address()));
670
671 if (field_trials_->announce_goog_ping) {
672 // Check if request contains a announce-request.
673 auto goog_misc = request->GetUInt16List(STUN_ATTR_GOOG_MISC_INFO);
674 if (goog_misc != nullptr &&
675 goog_misc->Size() >= kSupportGoogPingVersionRequestIndex &&
676 // Which version can we handle...currently any >= 1
677 goog_misc->GetType(kSupportGoogPingVersionRequestIndex) >= 1) {
678 auto list =
679 StunAttribute::CreateUInt16ListAttribute(STUN_ATTR_GOOG_MISC_INFO);
680 list->AddTypeAtIndex(kSupportGoogPingVersionResponseIndex,
681 kGoogPingVersion);
682 response.AddAttribute(std::move(list));
683 }
684 }
685
686 response.AddMessageIntegrity(local_candidate().password());
687 response.AddFingerprint();
688
689 SendResponseMessage(response);
690}
691
692void Connection::SendGoogPingResponse(const StunMessage* request) {
693 RTC_DCHECK(request->type() == GOOG_PING_REQUEST);
694
695 // Fill in the response message.
696 StunMessage response;
697 response.SetType(GOOG_PING_RESPONSE);
698 response.SetTransactionID(request->transaction_id());
699 response.AddMessageIntegrity32(local_candidate().password());
700 SendResponseMessage(response);
701}
702
703void Connection::SendResponseMessage(const StunMessage& response) {
704 // Where I send the response.
705 const rtc::SocketAddress& addr = remote_candidate_.address();
706
707 // Send the response message.
708 rtc::ByteBufferWriter buf;
709 response.Write(&buf);
710 rtc::PacketOptions options(port_->StunDscpValue());
711 options.info_signaled_after_sent.packet_type =
712 rtc::PacketType::kIceConnectivityCheckResponse;
713 auto err = port_->SendTo(buf.Data(), buf.Length(), addr, options, false);
714 if (err < 0) {
715 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << ToString() << ": Failed to send "
716 << StunMethodToString(response.type())
717 << ", to=" << addr.ToSensitiveString() << ", err=" << err
718 << ", id=" << rtc::hex_encode(response.transaction_id());
719 } else {
720 // Log at LS_INFO if we send a stun ping response on an unwritable
721 // connection.
722 rtc::LoggingSeverity sev = (!writable()) ? rtc::LS_INFO : rtc::LS_VERBOSE;
723 RTC_LOG_V(sev) << ToString() << ": Sent "
724 << StunMethodToString(response.type())
725 << ", to=" << addr.ToSensitiveString()
726 << ", id=" << rtc::hex_encode(response.transaction_id());
727
728 stats_.sent_ping_responses++;
729 LogCandidatePairEvent(webrtc::IceCandidatePairEventType::kCheckResponseSent,
730 response.reduced_transaction_id());
731 }
732}

734void Connection::OnReadyToSend() {
735 SignalReadyToSend(this);

738void Connection::Prune() {
739 if (!pruned_ || active()) {
740 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString() << ": Connection pruned";
741 pruned_ = true;
742 requests_.Clear();
743 set_write_state(STATE_WRITE_TIMEOUT);
744 }
745}

747void Connection::Destroy() {
748 // TODO(deadbeef, nisse): This may leak if an application closes a
749 // PeerConnection and then quickly destroys the PeerConnectionFactory (along
750 // with the networking thread on which this message is posted). Also affects
751 // tests, with a workaround in
752 // AutoSocketServerThread::~AutoSocketServerThread.
753 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << ToString() << ": Connection destroyed";
754 port_->thread()->Post(RTC_FROM_HERE, this, MSG_DELETE);
755 LogCandidatePairConfig(webrtc::IceCandidatePairConfigType::kDestroyed);
756}

768void Connection::PrintPingsSinceLastResponse(std::string* s, size_t max) {
769 rtc::StringBuilder oss;
770 if (pings_since_last_response_.size() > max) {
771 for (size_t i = 0; i < max; i++) {
772 const SentPing& ping = pings_since_last_response_[i];
773 oss << rtc::hex_encode(ping.id) << " ";
774 }
775 oss << "... " << (pings_since_last_response_.size() - max) << " more";
776 } else {
777 for (const SentPing& ping : pings_since_last_response_) {
778 oss << rtc::hex_encode(ping.id) << " ";
779 }
780 }
781 *s = oss.str();
782}
783
784void Connection::UpdateState(int64_t now) {
785 int rtt = ConservativeRTTEstimate(rtt_);
786
787 if (RTC_LOG_CHECK_LEVEL(LS_VERBOSE)) {
788 std::string pings;
789 PrintPingsSinceLastResponse(&pings, 5);
790 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << ToString()
791 << ": UpdateState()"
792 ", ms since last received response="
793 << now - last_ping_response_received_
794 << ", ms since last received data="
795 << now - last_data_received_ << ", rtt=" << rtt
796 << ", pings_since_last_response=" << pings;
797 }
798
799 // Check the writable state. (The order of these checks is important.)
800 //
801 // Before becoming unwritable, we allow for a fixed number of pings to fail
802 // (i.e., receive no response). We also have to give the response time to
803 // get back, so we include a conservative estimate of this.
804 //
805 // Before timing out writability, we give a fixed amount of time. This is to
806 // allow for changes in network conditions.
807
808 if ((write_state_ == STATE_WRITABLE) &&
809 TooManyFailures(pings_since_last_response_, unwritable_min_checks(), rtt,
810 now) &&
811 TooLongWithoutResponse(pings_since_last_response_, unwritable_timeout(),
812 now)) {
813 uint32_t max_pings = unwritable_min_checks();
814 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString() << ": Unwritable after " << max_pings
815 << " ping failures and "
816 << now - pings_since_last_response_[0].sent_time
817 << " ms without a response,"
818 " ms since last received ping="
819 << now - last_ping_received_
820 << " ms since last received data="
821 << now - last_data_received_ << " rtt=" << rtt;
822 set_write_state(STATE_WRITE_UNRELIABLE);
823 }
824 if ((write_state_ == STATE_WRITE_UNRELIABLE ||
825 write_state_ == STATE_WRITE_INIT) &&
826 TooLongWithoutResponse(pings_since_last_response_, inactive_timeout(),
827 now)) {
828 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString() << ": Timed out after "
829 << now - pings_since_last_response_[0].sent_time
830 << " ms without a response, rtt=" << rtt;
831 set_write_state(STATE_WRITE_TIMEOUT);
832 }
833
834 // Update the receiving state.
835 UpdateReceiving(now);
836 if (dead(now)) {
837 Destroy();
838 }
839}
840
841void Connection::Ping(int64_t now) {
842 last_ping_sent_ = now;
843 ConnectionRequest* req = new ConnectionRequest(this);
844 // If not using renomination, we use "1" to mean "nominated" and "0" to mean
845 // "not nominated". If using renomination, values greater than 1 are used for
846 // re-nominated pairs.
847 int nomination = use_candidate_attr_ ? 1 : 0;
848 if (nomination_ > 0) {
849 nomination = nomination_;
850 }
851 pings_since_last_response_.push_back(SentPing(req->id(), now, nomination));
852 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << ToString() << ": Sending STUN ping, id="
853 << rtc::hex_encode(req->id())
854 << ", nomination=" << nomination_;
855 requests_.Send(req);
856 state_ = IceCandidatePairState::IN_PROGRESS;
857 num_pings_sent_++;
858}
859
860void Connection::ReceivedPing(const absl::optional<std::string>& request_id) {
861 last_ping_received_ = rtc::TimeMillis();
862 last_ping_id_received_ = request_id;
863 UpdateReceiving(last_ping_received_);
864}
865
866void Connection::HandlePiggybackCheckAcknowledgementIfAny(StunMessage* msg) {
867 RTC_DCHECK(msg->type() == STUN_BINDING_REQUEST ||
868 msg->type() == GOOG_PING_REQUEST);
869 const StunByteStringAttribute* last_ice_check_received_attr =
870 msg->GetByteString(STUN_ATTR_GOOG_LAST_ICE_CHECK_RECEIVED);
871 if (last_ice_check_received_attr) {
872 const std::string request_id = last_ice_check_received_attr->GetString();
873 auto iter = absl::c_find_if(
874 pings_since_last_response_,
875 [&request_id](const SentPing& ping) { return ping.id == request_id; });
876 if (iter != pings_since_last_response_.end()) {
877 rtc::LoggingSeverity sev = !writable() ? rtc::LS_INFO : rtc::LS_VERBOSE;
878 RTC_LOG_V(sev) << ToString()
879 << ": Received piggyback STUN ping response, id="
880 << rtc::hex_encode(request_id);
881 const int64_t rtt = rtc::TimeMillis() - iter->sent_time;
882 ReceivedPingResponse(rtt, request_id, iter->nomination);
883 }
884 }
885}
886
887void Connection::ReceivedPingResponse(
888 int rtt,
889 const std::string& request_id,
890 const absl::optional<uint32_t>& nomination) {
891 RTC_DCHECK_GE(rtt, 0);
892 // We've already validated that this is a STUN binding response with
893 // the correct local and remote username for this connection.
894 // So if we're not already, become writable. We may be bringing a pruned
895 // connection back to life, but if we don't really want it, we can always
896 // prune it again.
897 if (nomination && nomination.value() > acked_nomination_) {
898 acked_nomination_ = nomination.value();
899 }
900
901 int64_t now = rtc::TimeMillis();
902 total_round_trip_time_ms_ += rtt;
903 current_round_trip_time_ms_ = static_cast<uint32_t>(rtt);
904 rtt_estimate_.AddSample(now, rtt);
905
906 pings_since_last_response_.clear();
907 last_ping_response_received_ = now;
908 UpdateReceiving(last_ping_response_received_);
909 set_write_state(STATE_WRITABLE);
910 set_state(IceCandidatePairState::SUCCEEDED);
911 if (rtt_samples_ > 0) {
912 rtt_ = rtc::GetNextMovingAverage(rtt_, rtt, RTT_RATIO);
913 } else {
914 rtt_ = rtt;
915 }
916 rtt_samples_++;
917}
918
919bool Connection::dead(int64_t now) const {
920 if (last_received() > 0) {
921 // If it has ever received anything, we keep it alive
922 // - if it has recevied last DEAD_CONNECTION_RECEIVE_TIMEOUT (30s)
923 // - if it has a ping outstanding shorter than
924 // DEAD_CONNECTION_RECEIVE_TIMEOUT (30s)
925 // - else if IDLE let it live field_trials_->dead_connection_timeout_ms
926 //
927 // This covers the normal case of a successfully used connection that stops
928 // working. This also allows a remote peer to continue pinging over a
929 // locally inactive (pruned) connection. This also allows the local agent to
930 // ping with longer interval than 30s as long as it shorter than
931 // |dead_connection_timeout_ms|.
932 if (now <= (last_received() + DEAD_CONNECTION_RECEIVE_TIMEOUT)) {
933 // Not dead since we have received the last 30s.
934 return false;
935 }
936 if (!pings_since_last_response_.empty()) {
937 // Outstanding pings: let it live until the ping is unreplied for
938 // DEAD_CONNECTION_RECEIVE_TIMEOUT.
939 return now > (pings_since_last_response_[0].sent_time +
940 DEAD_CONNECTION_RECEIVE_TIMEOUT);
941 }
942
943 // No outstanding pings: let it live until
944 // field_trials_->dead_connection_timeout_ms has passed.
945 return now > (last_received() + field_trials_->dead_connection_timeout_ms);
946 }
947
948 if (active()) {
949 // If it has never received anything, keep it alive as long as it is
950 // actively pinging and not pruned. Otherwise, the connection might be
951 // deleted before it has a chance to ping. This is the normal case for a
952 // new connection that is pinging but hasn't received anything yet.
953 return false;
954 }
955
956 // If it has never received anything and is not actively pinging (pruned), we
957 // keep it around for at least MIN_CONNECTION_LIFETIME to prevent connections
958 // from being pruned too quickly during a network change event when two
959 // networks would be up simultaneously but only for a brief period.
960 return now > (time_created_ms_ + MIN_CONNECTION_LIFETIME);
961}
962
963bool Connection::stable(int64_t now) const {
964 // A connection is stable if it's RTT has converged and it isn't missing any
965 // responses. We should send pings at a higher rate until the RTT converges
966 // and whenever a ping response is missing (so that we can detect
967 // unwritability faster)
968 return rtt_converged() && !missing_responses(now);
969}

980std::string Connection::ToString() const {
981 const absl::string_view CONNECT_STATE_ABBREV[2] = {
982 "-", // not connected (false)
983 "C", // connected (true)
984 };
985 const absl::string_view RECEIVE_STATE_ABBREV[2] = {
986 "-", // not receiving (false)
987 "R", // receiving (true)
988 };
989 const absl::string_view WRITE_STATE_ABBREV[4] = {
990 "W", // STATE_WRITABLE
991 "w", // STATE_WRITE_UNRELIABLE
992 "-", // STATE_WRITE_INIT
993 "x", // STATE_WRITE_TIMEOUT
994 };
995 const absl::string_view ICESTATE[4] = {
996 "W", // STATE_WAITING
997 "I", // STATE_INPROGRESS
998 "S", // STATE_SUCCEEDED
999 "F" // STATE_FAILED
1000 };
1001 const absl::string_view SELECTED_STATE_ABBREV[2] = {
1002 "-", // candidate pair not selected (false)
1003 "S", // selected (true)
1004 };
1005 const Candidate& local = local_candidate();
1006 const Candidate& remote = remote_candidate();
1007 rtc::StringBuilder ss;
1008 ss << "Conn[" << ToDebugId() << ":" << port_->content_name() << ":"
1009 << port_->Network()->ToString() << ":" << local.id() << ":"
1010 << local.component() << ":" << local.generation() << ":" << local.type()
1011 << ":" << local.protocol() << ":" << local.address().ToSensitiveString()
1012 << "->" << remote.id() << ":" << remote.component() << ":"
1013 << remote.priority() << ":" << remote.type() << ":" << remote.protocol()
1014 << ":" << remote.address().ToSensitiveString() << "|"
1015 << CONNECT_STATE_ABBREV[connected()] << RECEIVE_STATE_ABBREV[receiving()]
1016 << WRITE_STATE_ABBREV[write_state()] << ICESTATE[static_cast<int>(state())]
1017 << "|" << SELECTED_STATE_ABBREV[selected()] << "|" << remote_nomination()
1018 << "|" << nomination() << "|" << priority() << "|";
1019 if (rtt_ < DEFAULT_RTT) {
1020 ss << rtt_ << "]";
1021 } else {
1022 ss << "-]";
1023 }
1024 return ss.Release();
1025}

1033 return log_description_.value();

1035 const Candidate& local = local_candidate();
1036 const Candidate& remote = remote_candidate();
1037 const rtc::Network* network = port()->Network();
1038 log_description_ = webrtc::IceCandidatePairDescription();
1039 log_description_->local_candidate_type =
1040 GetCandidateTypeByString(local.type());
1041 log_description_->local_relay_protocol =

1043 log_description_->local_network_type = ConvertNetworkType(network->type());
1044 log_description_->local_address_family =

1048 log_description_->remote_address_family =

1070
1071void Connection::OnConnectionRequestResponse(ConnectionRequest* request,
1072 StunMessage* response) {
1073 // Log at LS_INFO if we receive a ping response on an unwritable
1074 // connection.
1075 rtc::LoggingSeverity sev = !writable() ? rtc::LS_INFO : rtc::LS_VERBOSE;
1076
1077 int rtt = request->Elapsed();
1078
1079 if (RTC_LOG_CHECK_LEVEL_V(sev)) {
1080 std::string pings;
1081 PrintPingsSinceLastResponse(&pings, 5);
1082 RTC_LOG_V(sev) << ToString() << ": Received "
1083 << StunMethodToString(response->type())
1084 << ", id=" << rtc::hex_encode(request->id())
1085 << ", code=0" // Makes logging easier to parse.
1086 ", rtt="
1087 << rtt << ", pings_since_last_response=" << pings;
1088 }
1089 absl::optional<uint32_t> nomination;
1090 const std::string request_id = request->id();
1091 auto iter = absl::c_find_if(
1092 pings_since_last_response_,
1093 [&request_id](const SentPing& ping) { return ping.id == request_id; });
1094 if (iter != pings_since_last_response_.end()) {
1095 nomination.emplace(iter->nomination);
1096 }
1097 ReceivedPingResponse(rtt, request_id, nomination);
1098
1099 stats_.recv_ping_responses++;
1100 LogCandidatePairEvent(
1101 webrtc::IceCandidatePairEventType::kCheckResponseReceived,
1102 response->reduced_transaction_id());
1103
1104 if (request->msg()->type() == STUN_BINDING_REQUEST) {
1105 if (!remote_support_goog_ping_.has_value()) {
1106 auto goog_misc = response->GetUInt16List(STUN_ATTR_GOOG_MISC_INFO);
1107 if (goog_misc != nullptr &&
1108 goog_misc->Size() >= kSupportGoogPingVersionResponseIndex) {
1109 // The remote peer has indicated that it {does/does not} supports
1110 // GOOG_PING.
1111 remote_support_goog_ping_ =
1112 goog_misc->GetType(kSupportGoogPingVersionResponseIndex) >=
1113 kGoogPingVersion;
1114 } else {
1115 remote_support_goog_ping_ = false;
1116 }
1117 }
1118
1119 MaybeUpdateLocalCandidate(request, response);
1120
1121 if (field_trials_->enable_goog_ping && remote_support_goog_ping_) {
1122 cached_stun_binding_ = request->msg()->Clone();
1123 }
1124 }
1125}
1126
1127void Connection::OnConnectionRequestErrorResponse(ConnectionRequest* request,
1128 StunMessage* response) {
1129 int error_code = response->GetErrorCodeValue();
1130 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << ToString() << ": Received "
1131 << StunMethodToString(response->type())
1132 << " id=" << rtc::hex_encode(request->id())
1133 << " code=" << error_code
1134 << " rtt=" << request->Elapsed();
1135
1136 cached_stun_binding_.reset();
1137 if (error_code == STUN_ERROR_UNKNOWN_ATTRIBUTE ||
1138 error_code == STUN_ERROR_SERVER_ERROR ||
1139 error_code == STUN_ERROR_UNAUTHORIZED) {
1140 // Recoverable error, retry
1141 } else if (error_code == STUN_ERROR_STALE_CREDENTIALS) {
1142 // Race failure, retry
1143 } else if (error_code == STUN_ERROR_ROLE_CONFLICT) {
1144 HandleRoleConflictFromPeer();
1145 } else if (request->msg()->type() == GOOG_PING_REQUEST) {
1146 // Race, retry.
1147 } else {
1148 // This is not a valid connection.
1149 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << ToString()
1150 << ": Received STUN error response, code=" << error_code
1151 << "; killing connection";
1152 FailAndDestroy();
1153 }
1154}

1156void Connection::OnConnectionRequestTimeout(ConnectionRequest* request) {
1157 // Log at LS_INFO if we miss a ping on a writable connection.
1158 rtc::LoggingSeverity sev = writable() ? rtc::LS_INFO : rtc::LS_VERBOSE;
1159 RTC_LOG_V(sev) << ToString() << ": Timing-out STUN ping "
1160 << rtc::hex_encode(request->id()) << " after "
1161 << request->Elapsed() << " ms";
1162}
1163
1164void Connection::OnConnectionRequestSent(ConnectionRequest* request) {
1165 // Log at LS_INFO if we send a ping on an unwritable connection.
1166 rtc::LoggingSeverity sev = !writable() ? rtc::LS_INFO : rtc::LS_VERBOSE;
1167 RTC_LOG_V(sev) << ToString() << ": Sent "
1168 << StunMethodToString(request->msg()->type())
1169 << ", id=" << rtc::hex_encode(request->id())
1170 << ", use_candidate=" << use_candidate_attr()
1171 << ", nomination=" << nomination();
1172 stats_.sent_ping_requests_total++;
1173 LogCandidatePairEvent(webrtc::IceCandidatePairEventType::kCheckSent,
1174 request->reduced_transaction_id());
1175 if (stats_.recv_ping_responses == 0) {
1176 stats_.sent_ping_requests_before_first_response++;
1177 }
1178}

1184void Connection::MaybeSetRemoteIceParametersAndGeneration(
1185 const IceParameters& ice_params,
1186 int generation) {
1187 if (remote_candidate_.username() == ice_params.ufrag &&
1188 remote_candidate_.password().empty()) {
1189 remote_candidate_.set_password(ice_params.pwd);
1190 }
1191 // TODO(deadbeef): A value of '0' for the generation is used for both
1192 // generation 0 and "generation unknown". It should be changed to an
1193 // absl::optional to fix this.
1194 if (remote_candidate_.username() == ice_params.ufrag &&
1195 remote_candidate_.password() == ice_params.pwd &&
1196 remote_candidate_.generation() == 0) {
1197 remote_candidate_.set_generation(generation);
1198 }
1199}

1201void Connection::MaybeUpdatePeerReflexiveCandidate(
1202 const Candidate& new_candidate) {
1203 if (remote_candidate_.type() == PRFLX_PORT_TYPE &&
1204 new_candidate.type() != PRFLX_PORT_TYPE &&
1205 remote_candidate_.protocol() == new_candidate.protocol() &&
1206 remote_candidate_.address() == new_candidate.address() &&
1207 remote_candidate_.username() == new_candidate.username() &&
1208 remote_candidate_.password() == new_candidate.password() &&
1209 remote_candidate_.generation() == new_candidate.generation()) {

1211 }

1226
1227ConnectionInfo Connection::stats() {
1228 stats_.recv_bytes_second = round(recv_rate_tracker_.ComputeRate());
1229 stats_.recv_total_bytes = recv_rate_tracker_.TotalSampleCount();
1230 stats_.sent_bytes_second = round(send_rate_tracker_.ComputeRate());
1231 stats_.sent_total_bytes = send_rate_tracker_.TotalSampleCount();
1232 stats_.receiving = receiving_;
1233 stats_.writable = write_state_ == STATE_WRITABLE;
1234 stats_.timeout = write_state_ == STATE_WRITE_TIMEOUT;
1235 stats_.new_connection = !reported_;
1236 stats_.rtt = rtt_;
1237 stats_.key = this;
1238 stats_.state = state_;
1239 stats_.priority = priority();
1240 stats_.nominated = nominated();
1241 stats_.total_round_trip_time_ms = total_round_trip_time_ms_;
1242 stats_.current_round_trip_time_ms = current_round_trip_time_ms_;
1243 stats_.local_candidate = local_candidate();
1244 stats_.remote_candidate = remote_candidate();
1245 return stats_;
1246}
1247
1248void Connection::MaybeUpdateLocalCandidate(ConnectionRequest* request,
1249 StunMessage* response) {
1250 // RFC 5245
1251 // The agent checks the mapped address from the STUN response. If the
1252 // transport address does not match any of the local candidates that the
1253 // agent knows about, the mapped address represents a new candidate -- a
1254 // peer reflexive candidate.
1255 const StunAddressAttribute* addr =
1256 response->GetAddress(STUN_ATTR_XOR_MAPPED_ADDRESS);
1257 if (!addr) {
1258 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
1259 << "Connection::OnConnectionRequestResponse - "
1260 "No MAPPED-ADDRESS or XOR-MAPPED-ADDRESS found in the "
1261 "stun response message";
1262 return;
1263 }
1264
1265 for (size_t i = 0; i < port_->Candidates().size(); ++i) {
1266 if (port_->Candidates()[i].address() == addr->GetAddress()) {
1267 if (local_candidate_index_ != i) {
1268 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString()
1269 << ": Updating local candidate type to srflx.";
1270 local_candidate_index_ = i;
1271 // SignalStateChange to force a re-sort in P2PTransportChannel as this
1272 // Connection's local candidate has changed.
1273 SignalStateChange(this);
1274 }
1275 return;
1276 }
1277 }
1278
1279 // RFC 5245
1280 // Its priority is set equal to the value of the PRIORITY attribute
1281 // in the Binding request.
1282 const StunUInt32Attribute* priority_attr =
1283 request->msg()->GetUInt32(STUN_ATTR_PRIORITY);
1284 if (!priority_attr) {
1285 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Connection::OnConnectionRequestResponse - "
1286 "No STUN_ATTR_PRIORITY found in the "
1287 "stun response message";
1288 return;
1289 }
1290 const uint32_t priority = priority_attr->value();
1291 std::string id = rtc::CreateRandomString(8);
1292
1293 // Create a peer-reflexive candidate based on the local candidate.
1294 Candidate new_local_candidate(local_candidate());
1295 new_local_candidate.set_id(id);
1296 new_local_candidate.set_type(PRFLX_PORT_TYPE);
1297 new_local_candidate.set_address(addr->GetAddress());
1298 new_local_candidate.set_priority(priority);
1299 new_local_candidate.set_related_address(local_candidate().address());
1300 new_local_candidate.set_foundation(Port::ComputeFoundation(
1301 PRFLX_PORT_TYPE, local_candidate().protocol(),
1302 local_candidate().relay_protocol(), local_candidate().address()));
1303
1304 // Change the local candidate of this Connection to the new prflx candidate.
1305 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString() << ": Updating local candidate type to prflx.";
1306 local_candidate_index_ = port_->AddPrflxCandidate(new_local_candidate);
1307
1308 // SignalStateChange to force a re-sort in P2PTransportChannel as this
1309 // Connection's local candidate has changed.
1310 SignalStateChange(this);
1311}
1312
1313bool Connection::rtt_converged() const {
1314 return rtt_samples_ > (RTT_RATIO + 1);
1315}
1316
1317bool Connection::missing_responses(int64_t now) const {
1318 if (pings_since_last_response_.empty()) {
1319 return false;
1320 }
1321
1322 int64_t waiting = now - pings_since_last_response_[0].sent_time;
1323 return waiting > 2 * rtt();
1324}
1325
1326bool Connection::TooManyOutstandingPings(
1327 const absl::optional<int>& max_outstanding_pings) const {
1328 if (!max_outstanding_pings.has_value()) {
1329 return false;
1330 }
1331 if (static_cast<int>(pings_since_last_response_.size()) <
1332 *max_outstanding_pings) {
1333 return false;
1334 }
1335 return true;
1336}
1337
1338bool Connection::ShouldSendGoogPing(const StunMessage* message) {
1339 if (remote_support_goog_ping_ == true && cached_stun_binding_ &&
1340 cached_stun_binding_->EqualAttributes(message, [](int type) {
1341 // Ignore these attributes.
1342 // NOTE: Consider what to do if adding more content to
1343 // STUN_ATTR_GOOG_MISC_INFO
1344 return type != STUN_ATTR_FINGERPRINT &&
1345 type != STUN_ATTR_MESSAGE_INTEGRITY &&
1346 type != STUN_ATTR_RETRANSMIT_COUNT &&
1347 type != STUN_ATTR_GOOG_MISC_INFO;
1348 })) {
1349 return true;
1350 }
1351 return false;
1352}
1353
1354void Connection::ForgetLearnedState() {
1355 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString() << ": Connection forget learned state";
1356 requests_.Clear();
1357 receiving_ = false;
1358 write_state_ = STATE_WRITE_INIT;
1359 rtt_estimate_.Reset();
1360 pings_since_last_response_.clear();
1361}

1363ProxyConnection::ProxyConnection(Port* port,
1364 size_t index,
1365 const Candidate& remote_candidate)
1366 : Connection(port, index, remote_candidate) {}
1367
1368int ProxyConnection::Send(const void* data,
1369 size_t size,
1370 const rtc::PacketOptions& options) {
1371 stats_.sent_total_packets++;
1372 int sent =
1373 port_->SendTo(data, size, remote_candidate_.address(), options, true);
1374 int64_t now = rtc::TimeMillis();
1375 if (sent <= 0) {
1376 RTC_DCHECK(sent < 0);
1377 error_ = port_->GetError();
1378 stats_.sent_discarded_packets++;
1379 } else {
1380 send_rate_tracker_.AddSamplesAtTime(now, sent);
1381 }
1382 last_send_data_ = now;
1383 return sent;
1384}
1385
1386int ProxyConnection::GetError() {
1387 return error_;
1388}
